                    The Complete Nmap Ethical Hacking Course : Network Security
                    Course Notes Part 1


                    Section 1 - Introduction
1 - Introduction to instructor (BIO)
Brief intro to the course author/instructor

2 - Target Audience
The course is designed for anyone wishing to know more about NMap
Students should know something about OS, Networking, Security etc
NMap is a very important piece of software for security people to know

3 - What is Nmap
NMap which is short for Network Mapper 
  - Is a free and open source command line tool for network discover and security assessments
  - https://nmap.org
  - It is used by a wide variety of IT people including Penetration Testers & System Administrators
  - It is also a port scanner with more functionality then other port scanners
  - NMap allows for the use of scripts, it use the LUA language
  - It runs on all major OS
  - The GUI is called Zenmap and will be covered in the course

4 - Goals and Learning Objectives
What the student is expected to learn from the course



