                    Section 3 – Installing Nmap and Cloud Labs
1 - Goals and Learning Objectives
What the student is expected to learn from the section

2 - How to Install Nmap
NMap is available for most platforms
To install on Linux
  - sudo apt-get install nmap
The instructor recommends running NMap from Kali Linux
  - https://www.kali.org/downloads/
  - It is a pen-testing tool based on Debian
  - You can use VMware or Virtual Box to install on a virtual machine
Some versions of Linux come with NMap pre-installed
  - nmap --version at the command line to check to see if it is installed
  - Preinstalled versions maybe older so will need updating
  - There are source code packages available which can be used to build an install
    - These are often quicker etc because they are built closer to your machine specs

3 - Cloud Based Hacking Lab
A quick guide on how to setup a server to do NMap scans from your own server on the internet
  - This maybe necessary if there are restricitions on scan traffic
  - This example uses Digital Ocean as a host
  - You can install the full version of Kali on AWS
    - There is a free Amazon Machine Instance (AMI) on the marketplace which can be installed quickly



                    Section 4 – Nmap Basics, Target Specification & Port States
1 - Goals and Learning Objectives
What the student is expected to learn from the section

2 - An Introduction to Port Scanning and Fingerprinting
A few quick notes about scanning
  - In some countries port scanning is illegal
  - NMap scripts that extend functionality may cross into illegality when scanning
  - Scanning happens all the time on the internet
    - It is similar to looking at a house to see what the windows, doors etc are like
There are also some alternatives to NMap available
  - For companies with large IP address ranges -- ZMap, Masscan
  - For fingerprinting websites -- WhatWeb, BlindElephant
More information on these tools and more is available at the Kali tools website
  - https://tools.kali.org

